wikipedia_page.main: Frederick James Bowley (20 February 1909 – October 1994) was an English first-class cricketer, born at Ratby, Leicestershire. He played primarily for Leicestershire in 1930–1931, batting right-handed and bowling slow left-arm orthodox. He died in October 1994 at Leicester.
